kinetic.client

Class EntryMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • kinetic.client.EntryMetadata

  • public class EntryMetadata
extends java.lang.Object
    Kinetic Entry Metadata container.

    A Kinetic entry contains key, value, and entry metadata.

    Kinetic applications use KineticClient API to perform Entry operations. Such as KineticClient.putForced(Entry) to store an Entry in the Kinetic store.

    Applications may also use KineticClient.getMetadata(byte[]) or KineticClient.getMetadataAsync(byte[], CallbackHandler) to obtain entry metadata information.

    Author:
    James Hughes., Chiaming Yang
    See Also:
    Entry, KineticClient
